Makes 10Ingredients:500g lamb mince1 small red onion, finely chopped15ml (1 tbsp) ready-made basil pesto45ml (3 tbsp) chopped fresh mintSalt and pepper1 large egg, lightly beatenOlive oil, for frying10 mini pita breads1 tub ready-made hummus (or make your own using the recipe below)1 tub ready-made tzatzikiMethod:1. Combine the mince, onion, pesto and mint, mix well and season. Add the egg and mix until well combined.2. Roll the mince mixture into 10 balls (this is easier if you wet your hands). Flatten the balls slightly to form patties3. Fry on both sides in a little hot olive oil until cooked to your liking. Serve the patties in the mini pita breads with dollops of hummus and tzatziki, with trimmings and salad if desired.How to your own hummus Place 1 can of drained and rinsed chickpeas, 2-3 cloves chopped garlic, the juice of 1 lemon, 1/3 cup olive oil, 1/3 cup tahini and 1 tsp ground cumin in a food processor. Blend until smooth, adding more oil if needed. Season to taste with salt and black pepper. Spoon into a bowl and drizzle with extra olive oil before serving.